ZH: 他一见到我就滔滔不绝地说了一个小时。
EN: He started talking non-stop for an hour as soon as he saw me.

ZH: 她滔滔不绝地讲述了她的新鲜经历。
EN: She went on and on about her exciting experience.

ZH: 他们两个朋友滔滔不绝地交谈着，好像从来停不下来。
EN: The two friends chatted incessantly as if they would never stop.

ZH: 我小时候常常看见爷爷滔滔不绝地给我们讲故事。
EN: When I was young, I often saw my grandfather telling us stories without stopping.

ZH: 她问了一个问题后，老师就滔滔不绝地解释了一个小时。
EN: After she asked a question, the teacher explained for an hour continuously.

ZH: 他一上台就滔滔不绝地演讲了一个小时。
EN: He gave a non-stop speech for an hour as soon as he stepped on the stage.

ZH: 这位导游滔滔不绝地向我们介绍了这座城市的历史。
EN: The tour guide went on and on about the history of this city.

ZH: 她滔滔不绝地向我抱怨了她的工作。
EN: She complained non-stop to me about her job.

ZH: 我们在那个晚会上聊得滔滔不绝，非常开心。
EN: We chatted non-stop at that party and had a great time.

ZH: 父亲滔滔不绝地教育我们要有耐心和恒心。
EN: Father educated us tirelessly on the importance of patience and perseverance.

ZH: 她滔滔不绝地吐露了自己的内心感受。
EN: She poured out her inner feelings non-stop.

ZH: 他滔滔不绝地哄着孩子们入睡。
EN: He talked non-stop to lull the children to sleep.

ZH: 我们经过了一个星期的滔滔不绝的大雨。
EN: We experienced a week of non-stop heavy rain.

ZH: 他在报告中滔滔不绝地阐述了自己的观点。
EN: He elaborated on his views non-stop in the report.

ZH: 她听说这个消息后，滔滔不绝地问了一连串问题。
EN: After she heard the news, she bombarded with a series of questions non-stop.

ZH: 这位老人滔滔不绝地回忆起自己的年轻时光。
EN: The old man reminisced about his youth non-stop.

ZH: 他滔滔不绝地赞扬了这个新产品的优点。
EN: He spoke non-stop to praise the advantages of this new product.

ZH: 他太为自己的成就而自豪，一直滔滔不绝地说个不停。
EN: He was so proud of his achievements that he kept boasting non-stop.

ZH: 她太兴奋了，一回家就滔滔不绝地给朋友们讲述了她的经历。
EN: She was so excited that she couldn't stop telling her friends about her experience as soon as she got home.

ZH: 这个会议持续了一整天，每个人都滔滔不绝地发言。
EN: The meeting lasted the whole day, and everyone spoke non-stop.
